<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!DOCTYPE rpl PUBLIC "-//ROCKLYTE//DTD RPL 1.0//EN">

<body face="Noto Sans" font-size="11pt" margins="28"/>

<page name="Index">
   <h1>Long Word Benchmark</h1>

   <p>This paragraph is designed to force repeated word-width accumulation and difficult wrapping decisions. The token
   supercalifragilisticexpialidocious_benchmark_segment_alpha_beta_gamma_delta_epsilon_zeta_eta_theta_iota_kappa_lambda
   appears inside otherwise normal text so the surrounding line state must still be handled correctly.</p>

   <p>A second paragraph repeats the same pattern with another deliberately large token:
   documentation_performance_refactor_measurement_sequence_with_embedded_identifiers_and_no_natural_break_positions
   and then continues with enough trailing text to force the line to resume normal wrapping after any width extension
   or restart has occurred.</p>

   <p no-wrap>This final paragraph disables wrapping and contains the token
   no_wrap_layout_width_extension_probe_token_with_multiple_repeated_sections_for_page_growth_validation so that page
   width extension paths can be exercised deterministically.</p>
</page>
